post_text:
Hello Miami Families,
We are excited to inform you that educational packets will be available today. We will have academic work on each van during meal deliveries. Please check delivery times on the website or call Lori at 928-425-3271 x1363. We will also have packets available at Bejarano School between 10:30 and 12:30. We will continue to provide work in this manner each Tuesday. You can return the work the following Tuesday when you pick up the next packet. Should your child complete the work earlier, you can send it back with the van and we will get it to your child’s teacher.

Last week, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman extended school closures through April 10, 2020. I will continue to send updates as they become available to us. Please stay at home and healthy during this time. We care about the families we serve and hope you are all well.
Thank you for your continued understanding.

Safety is No Accident, Over the Counter Medication Safety Class for Parents November 20th 2019.

There will be an Over the Counter Medication Safety Class for parents on Wednesday, November 20th at the Lee Kornegay middle school at 5:30 pm in the school library. The cost to enter is free of charge. Safety tips for locking up medications will be discussed. A Doctor of Pharmacy from the Cobre Valley Regional Medical Center will be available to answer questions. The first ten parents at the door will get a prize. This class has been sponsored by the Parent Engagement Grant, Miami High School and the Cobre Valley Regional Medical Center.

For questions, please contact Pat at Miami High School at (928) 425-3271, ext. 5110.

post_text: Ms. Canez was a loved friend, teacher, co-worker and community member. She started her career with Miami Unified School District over 26 years ago as a general education teacher and then moved into special education. Ms. Canez had a kind heart and gave her all to her family and students. Her ability to encourage her students to be better than they thought possible and the friendship she provided, leaves a legacy to all of us. Her sense of humor, dedication, and ability to teach will be greatly missed. We are a family here at Miami Unified School District and Ms. Canez will be missed by all. Our prayers go out to her family, friends, and students during this difficult time.

Officers have completed their investigation of this morning’s report of a possible weapon in the Miami Junior Senior High School parking lot. No weapon was found. The lockdown at all schools has been lifted and school has resumed as normal.
text:
Update:

Officers have completed their investigation of this morning’s report of a possible weapon in the Miami Junior Senior High School parking lot. No weapon was found. The lockdown at all schools has been lifted and school has resumed as normal.

post_text: We received notice this morning of a possible weapon in the parking lot. A lockout was immediately put into place and students moved to a safe and secure area. A lockout will continue while the officers continue their investigation. Students are now attending classes as usual but will be kept within the building. A message will be sent when the lockout has been lifted. Thank you for your patience.

post_text:
===== PUBLIC NOTICE =====

All students look forward to benchmarks in their education such as 8th grade promotion and graduation.

With the incident that occurred at Miami Junior Senior High School this week, we will be implementing the following procedures for 8th grade promotion scheduled for May 24th at 9am.

The day of 8th grade promotion there will be additional security through the generosity of the Gila County Sheriffs Office. The District will be asking all visitors to park in the student parking lot (located on the west side of the auditorium). Visitors will enter the auditorium using the west lobby doors. Please do not bring oversize bags into the auditorium. As a reminder, no food or drink is allowed in the auditorium.

Following these guidelines will assist us in making the 8th grade promotion an event that will be enjoyed as always, and a cherished memory.

If you have any questions please call 928-425-3271

post_text:
=====PUBLIC NOTICE=====

On May 14, 2018 an incident was reported to the Miami Junior Senior High School principal in the early afternoon. The report consisted of two students that may have had weapons and were making threats. Within 90 seconds of the report, the two students were apprehended. An investigation was completed and the students have been removed from school for the remainder of the year.

Based on the possible threats, the Gila County Sheriff’s office has committed to have additional officers on campus during eighth grade promotion.

To All MUSD Parents and Community,

In order to allow any staff member who would like to participate in the Walk Out, the District will be closing schools on Thursday April 26th. We will resume school on Monday April 30, 2018 as long as we have sufficient staff to supervise students.

The make-up day will be May 18th.

Sincerely,

Sherry Dorathy, Ed.D.

Dear Parents of Miami Junior-Senior High School,

We are going through our accreditation process with AdvancEd. This used to be called the North Central Association, and happens every five years.

Part of the process is to survey our students, staff and families. The process is now online, and we are hoping you will take five minutes to complete the anonymous survey.

Please go to:
http://eprovesurveys.advanc ed.org/surveys/#/action/47745/7692

post_text:
The Gila County Public Health department provides flu shots at your child’s school. Each year the vaccine changes to address the current strain of flu circulating. This year’s vaccine covers four flu strains, so it is important for you to provide your child with this protection. We provide the inactive, injectable, and preservative free vaccine only.

If you are interested in your child participating in his/her school clinic, please fill out the attached form below and turn it in to either your school or local health department.

Flu clinics scheduled for all schools
Lee Kornegay is Wed. Sept 20th @ 9:00 AM
CAB is Wed. Sept 27th @ 9:00 AM
MJSHS is Mon. Oct 2nd @ 9:00 AM
